228
00:12:57,736 --> 00:13:01,198
"within thirteen days of each other,
then the user will die..."

229
00:13:02,700 --> 00:13:05,119
<i>Light Yagami and Misa Amane
are alive...</i>

230
00:13:06,537 --> 00:13:07,579
<i>Thirteen days...</i>

231
00:13:08,580 --> 00:13:09,581
<i>This is the only...</i>

232
00:13:16,672 --> 00:13:20,092
<i>The following is the record which
contains everything</i>

233
00:13:20,175 --> 00:13:22,469
<i>I have investigated
on the Kira incident.</i>

234
00:13:23,595 --> 00:13:26,140
<i>The fact that you are
reading this message means</i>

235
00:13:27,057 --> 00:13:29,810
<i>I am no longer alive at this moment.</i>

236
00:13:30,894 --> 00:13:35,733
I hereby leave this record
as my firm achievement.

237
00:14:01,175 --> 00:14:03,344
It's been ten days since
Ryuzaki's secret funeral...

238
00:14:03,635 --> 00:14:05,846
It looks like we aren't going to die...

239
00:14:06,805 --> 00:14:09,141
We now know Watari's identity,
but in the end,

240
00:14:09,308 --> 00:14:11,143
we didn't find out anything
about Ryuzaki...

241
00:14:11,810 --> 00:14:15,397
It seems Watari was actually
an amazing inventor.

242
00:14:16,023 --> 00:14:18,442
He created orphanages worldwide

243
00:14:18,650 --> 00:14:20,986
with the fortune built on
numerous patents.

244
00:14:21,612 --> 00:14:23,489
He's a hero! A hero!

245
00:14:23,864 --> 00:14:29,620
But we can't continue investigating here
now that L and Watari are gone...

246
00:14:30,079 --> 00:14:31,163
This is tough...

247
00:14:31,538 --> 00:14:32,581
Hmm...

248
00:14:32,706 --> 00:14:33,832
Light, how is it going?

249
00:14:34,500 --> 00:14:38,462
I can remove the entire system
here by tonight.

250
00:14:39,505 --> 00:14:41,548
I don't feel good about it.
It feels like stealing.

251
00:14:42,466 --> 00:14:45,219
I've created a voice like
the one that Ryuzaki used.

252
00:14:45,594 --> 00:14:46,887
We can act like he's still alive

253
00:14:47,221 --> 00:14:50,224
and control the police
as we've been doing, but...

254
00:14:50,849 --> 00:14:54,186
Who will replace L?
Where will we do it?

255
00:14:54,686 --> 00:14:56,188
What'll we do with
the killer notebook?

256
00:14:56,688 --> 00:14:58,399
What are you talking about, Light?!

257
00:14:58,524 --> 00:15:00,651
The only one who can take on
the role of L is you!

258
00:15:04,363 --> 00:15:07,908
If Ryuzaki was killed by Kira
for challenging him...

259
00:15:08,409 --> 00:15:09,701
I don't feel comfortable about it.

260
00:15:10,536 --> 00:15:13,330
Besides that, I'll be tricking
the people of the world...

261
00:15:14,164 --> 00:15:17,418
I understand your feelings,
but you're the only one who can do this.

262
00:15:17,876 --> 00:15:20,295
That's right. Ryuzaki even said so...

263
00:15:20,754 --> 00:15:22,798
You'd be capable of succeeding L.

264
00:15:25,676 --> 00:15:30,389
<i>So easy...
It's no fun without Ryuzaki...</i>

265
00:15:31,974 --> 00:15:33,725
Yeah, all right. I'll do it.

266
00:15:35,894 --> 00:15:37,646
But I won't do anything dangerous

267
00:15:37,729 --> 00:15:41,817
like challenging Kira directly
in order to gain clues, like Ryuzaki did.

268
00:15:42,192 --> 00:15:43,277
Is that okay?

269
00:15:43,610 --> 00:15:46,530
Yes. That would be better and safer.

270
00:15:47,239 --> 00:15:49,408
Ryuzaki might have been
too confrontational...

271
00:15:49,867 --> 00:15:50,868
In that case...

272
00:15:51,243 --> 00:15:55,330
I can do about the same work
with this computer and my own.

273
00:15:56,039 --> 00:15:58,500
It's also possible to be L
from my room at home.

274
00:15:59,710 --> 00:16:00,794
I'll also be Watari.

275
00:16:01,753 --> 00:16:04,590
But it would be difficult to do this
with my mom and little sister around.

276
00:16:06,258 --> 00:16:08,760
It would be good if I could rent
a one-room apartment.

277
00:16:09,136 --> 00:16:13,932
There's nothing suspicious about renting
a room for my son to live on his own.

278
00:16:14,349 --> 00:16:15,476
That's right.

279
00:16:15,726 --> 00:16:19,438
Then the place he'll be renting out
will be the task force headquarters.

280
00:16:19,480 --> 00:16:20,522
Yes.

281
00:16:20,564 --> 00:16:23,275
All that's left is what to do
with the killer notebook...

282
00:16:23,609 --> 00:16:25,777
There's no need to think too hard...

283
00:16:26,445 --> 00:16:28,280
We'll just have one of the five of us,

284
00:16:28,363 --> 00:16:32,242
one who we trust will never
use the notebook...

285
00:16:32,326 --> 00:16:33,702
hide it somewhere
where no one can get to it.

286
00:16:35,621 --> 00:16:37,372
Chief, please do this!

287
00:16:38,123 --> 00:16:39,791
We can count on you!

288
00:16:40,417 --> 00:16:42,336
You're a pillar of justice!

289
00:16:43,420 --> 00:16:44,463
Me, huh?

290
00:16:45,672 --> 00:16:46,673
All right...

291
00:16:47,257 --> 00:16:48,842
Let's avenge Ryuzaki!

292
00:16:49,301 --> 00:16:50,344
Yeah.

293
00:16:50,469 --> 00:16:54,431
Yes. Kira's still here.
Let's catch him!

294
00:16:56,308 --> 00:17:00,145
Well then, let's have a party to
celebrate Light becoming the second L.

295
00:17:00,521 --> 00:17:02,564
Quit fooling around, now's not the time.

296
00:17:02,648 --> 00:17:03,690
Now, now...

297
00:17:11,990 --> 00:17:12,991
Light!

298
00:17:13,575 --> 00:17:17,371
It's our first date in a while.
Enjoy yourself a little more...

299
00:17:20,541 --> 00:17:21,542
Misa...

300
00:17:23,418 --> 00:17:24,586
Let's live together.

301
00:17:24,795 --> 00:17:25,837
Huh?!

302
00:17:26,672 --> 00:17:27,839
Really?!

303
00:17:28,382 --> 00:17:30,342
Yeah.
I've already rented an apartment.

304
00:17:32,386 --> 00:17:34,429
All right! We're living together!

305
00:17:34,513 --> 00:17:35,847
Misa wins!

306
00:17:36,014 --> 00:17:37,015
"Wins?"

307
00:17:37,099 --> 00:17:38,976
You know, against Kiyomi
and Mari and Yuri.

308
00:17:39,685 --> 00:17:41,144
It's all right, Light.

309
00:17:41,436 --> 00:17:44,022
You only used them to trick L,
didn't you?

310
00:17:44,231 --> 00:17:45,440
I understand.

311
00:17:45,691 --> 00:17:47,442
You won't see them anymore, will you?!

312
00:17:48,026 --> 00:17:49,111
Yeah...

313
00:17:56,034 --> 00:17:57,035
Hey...

314
00:17:57,494 --> 00:18:00,247
So is your score
finally settled with L?

315
00:18:01,081 --> 00:18:02,082
Yeah.

316
00:18:02,666 --> 00:18:06,044
So I shouldn't expect
anything interesting anymore...

317
00:18:08,922 --> 00:18:10,465
That's not true, Ryuk.

318
00:18:11,133 --> 00:18:12,134
Hm?

319
00:18:12,175 --> 00:18:13,218
From now on...

320
00:18:15,429 --> 00:18:17,639
I'll show you the creation
of a new world.

321
00:18:18,807 --> 00:18:19,850
Oh?

322
00:19:30,295 --> 00:19:31,296
Papa!

323
00:19:35,550 --> 00:19:36,551
Papa!

324
00:19:46,061 --> 00:19:47,729
Yotsuba's reconstruction
is just beginning.

325
00:19:48,146 --> 00:19:49,856
Yeah.
Let's do our best!

326
00:19:50,816 --> 00:19:51,858
Hm?

327
00:19:51,983 --> 00:19:53,652
Hey... Namikawa?

328
00:19:55,487 --> 00:19:57,155
Huh?! Impossible!

329
00:20:03,203 --> 00:20:08,458
<i>In April, 2012, Light Yagami,
age 23, joins the National Police Agency.</i>

330
00:20:09,167 --> 00:20:10,877
<i>In the summer of 2012,</i>

331
00:20:10,961 --> 00:20:14,131
<i>Kira's judgments
gain momentum.</i>

332
00:20:14,464 --> 00:20:20,011
<i>The world screams in fear of Kira,
but privately it cheers for him.</i>

333
00:20:20,095 --> 00:20:22,514
<i>Slowly, their true thoughts come out,</i>

334
00:20:22,597 --> 00:20:27,394
<i>and some countries even express
their acceptance of Kira.</i>

335
00:20:27,853 --> 00:20:32,190
<i>The world continues towards
a dark era where Kira is the law.</i>

336
00:21:11,480 --> 00:21:12,647
What is it, Roger?

337
00:21:17,694 --> 00:21:19,571
I is dead.

